"script": "Could you survive a storm where it rains solid diamonds? On Neptune, this actually happens. Deep inside the planet, crushing pressure squeezes carbon until it hardens into glittering gems that fall like hail. So imagine standing beneath that downpour. At first it sounds beautiful, a sky raining jewels. But each diamond plummets through air sixteen times denser than ours, building terrible speed. Then they'd strike you like a hail of bullets, not soft drops. And the temperature down there runs thousands of degrees, hot enough to roast you instantly. You'd be the richest person alive for half a second, then gone.",
